title: Touchet's Garcia Athlete of the Week
text: Print this article Advertisement RENTON, Wash. â€” Touchet senior football player Leo Garcia has been named the Washington Interscholastic Activities Association (WIAA) male Athlete of the Week in Class 1B-8 football play. Garcia led the Indians with 178 yards rushing, on 22 carries and four touchdowns. He also led the defense with 11 tackles and four sacks. In recognition of their accomplishment, each Athlete of the Week winner receives a congratulatory letter from WIAA Executive Director, Mike Colbrese, a commemorative WIAA State Athlete of the Week T-shirt, and a certificate. Winners are also posted to the WIAA website at www.wiaa.com.
